</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>ACR127:v97#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="ACR127"/><meta name="dc:title" content="ACR &#xA;              127-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Assembly Concurrent Resolution
              
                        No. 127</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 16</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to National School Counseling Week.</span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">March 19, 2026.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">ACR 127, Muratsuchi.
                          National School Counseling Week.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would recognize February 2, 2026, to February 6, 2026, inclusive, as National School Counseling Week.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_D774B8A8-6ABD-4B93-9DB4-62E2871D9A0E"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, School counselors are a vital part of the education system and play a significant role in ensuring that all pupils receive the support they need to be successful in school and in life; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_7F21D40D-29D7-4595-BB14-AD95C2FB91BE"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Annually, the nation sets aside the first week in February to recognize the unique contributions of school counselors with the 2026 theme being School Counselors Amplify Student Success; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_F86E28F3-FD5D-42C3-BFBA-091170A05FC1"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, California school counselors are employed in public and private schools to help pupils reach their full potential; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_A9667A25-ADCF-4F69-91F9-5FDC3BB7BFE1"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, All children and youth can learn with appropriate supports and have the fundamental right to an education that meets their individual needs; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_B82ED581-D83D-4433-9EBC-5DC2E4BD7B12"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Children’s mental health and resilience are closely interconnected with their learning and postsecondary success; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_D87FC56C-86AE-4DF1-B3A8-7854450263EF"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, School counselors provide services and coordinate programs that improve school climate and increase pupils’ sense of connectedness within the school setting; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_0F81725C-6B58-48CA-842D-5E22267EFA5D"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, School counselors deliver a range of services to reduce mental health stigma, identify risk factors and warning signs for pupils at risk of mental health and behavioral disorders, and provide counseling services that strengthen pupils’ prospects for success in school and life; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_2895AE65-69B5-440E-85FA-9B60E7D8038D"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, School counselors address trauma caused by racial injustice, economic inequity, discrimination based on disability, gender, sexual orientation, immigration status, and other systemic and societal injustices, and are uniquely positioned within school settings to promote equity, healing, and support for all pupils; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_BB2100D8-DB92-4E72-BE44-2277019BB58F"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, School counselors provide high-quality career education programs from transitional kindergarten through grade 12 that promote the connection between learning and future career choices, including career technical education; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_75DCA7C0-CAE8-4E37-90D4-4B106F8AEFF4"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, School counselors advise secondary pupils on satisfying the A–G curricular requirements for college admissions and encourage participation in college preparation programs, including, but not limited to, Advancement Via Individual Determination (AVID), Early College, and International Baccalaureate programs by increasing pupils’ awareness of careers aligned with their interests and talents so they may become productive members of society; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_0AE848FB-6321-488A-8347-0E1399658945"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, California school counselors support and consult with parents, teachers, and other educators to help youth explore their potential and set realistic goals; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_61630708-F9AB-49B8-B89E-A83539A04012"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The citizens of California should recognize the vital role that more than 13,500 school counselors play in the academic, career, social, and emotional development of the state’s children; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_1EB9A2AD-85AE-4056-9F77-C7067E91DF43"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, the Senate thereof concurring, That the Legislature hereby recognizes February 2, 2026, to February 6, 2026, inclusive, as National School Counseling Week; and be it further </div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_13C8A64A-3815-4AC6-910A-748B447CF309"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution. </div></span></span></div></body></html>
